Que 1) What are HTML Elements?
-------------------------------
HTML elements are the building blocks of a web page. 🧱
Every web page is made using many HTML elements.
An HTML element has 3 parts:
Opening Tag – tells the browser where the element starts
Content – the text or data inside the element
Closing Tag – tells the browser where the element ends
Example
<p>Interview Happy</p>
Explanation:
<p> → Opening tag
Interview Happy → Content
</p> → Closing tag
So the complete element is:
<p>Interview Happy</p>
Que 2) What is a Tag?
------------------------
A Tag is only the keyword inside < > brackets.
Example:
<p>      → Opening Tag
</p>     → Closing Tag
Tags do not contain content.
They only mark the start or end of an element.
3️⃣ Difference Between Element and Tag
Tag	Element
Part of HTML code	Complete structure
Written inside < >	Includes tag + content
Example: <p>	Example: <p>Hello</p>
Simple Example
Tag:
<p>
</p>
Element:
<p>Hello</p>
✅ One-line interview answer
HTML elements are the building blocks of web pages and consist of a start tag, content, and an end tag. A tag is
only the opening or closing part of an element.

Que 3)What is HTML?
-------------------
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard language used to create web pages. 🌐
It tells the browser how to display content like:
Text,Images,Links,Videos,Tables
Example
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>My Page</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Hello World</h1>
<p>This is my first webpage</p>
</body>
</html>
Here HTML uses tags to structure the page.
Que 4)Difference Between HTML and HTML5?
----------------------------------------
HTML	HTML5
Older version of HTML	Latest version
Limited multimedia support	Built-in audio & video support
Needs plugins like Flash	No plugins needed
Fewer semantic tags	New semantic tags added
Less support for mobile apps	Better for mobile applications
Example of New HTML5 Tags
<header>
<footer>
<section>
<article>
<nav>
These make the website more organized and readable.
3️⃣ Advantages of HTML5
1️⃣ Multimedia Support
HTML5 supports audio and video without plugins.
Example
<video controls>
<source src="movie.mp4">
</video>
2️⃣Better for Mobile Devices 📱
HTML5 works well on phones, tablets, and modern browsers.
3️⃣ New Semantic Tags
Tags like:
<header>
<footer>
<article>
make code clean and easy to understand.
4️⃣ Offline Storage
HTML5 can store data in the browser using:
Local Storage
Session Storage
5️⃣ Faster Performance ⚡
HTML5 pages load faster and smoother.
✅ Simple Interview Answer (Best)
HTML is the standard language used to create web pages.
HTML5 is the latest version of HTML that supports multimedia, new semantic tags, better performance, and mobile-friendly 
features.

Que 5) What is the difference between HTML and XHTML?
-------------------------------------------------------
HTML
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is used to create web pages.
It is flexible and less strict about rules.
Tags sometimes do not need to be closed.
Attribute values can be written without quotes.
Example:
<p>Hello World
<br>
XHTML
XHTML (Extensible HyperText Markup Language) is a stricter version of HTML.
It follows XML rules, so syntax must be very strict.
All tags must be closed.
Attribute values must be in quotes.
Tags must be properly nested and written in lowercase.
Example:
<p>Hello World</p>
<br />
Que 6) What is the role of DOCTYPE in HTML?
--------------------------------------------
Simple Explanation
DOCTYPE tells the web browser which version of HTML the page is using. 🌐
It helps the browser display the webpage correctly.
The DOCTYPE declaration is always written at the top of the HTML document before the <html> tag.
Example
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>My Page</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Hello</h1>
</body>
</html>
Here:
<!DOCTYPE html> → tells the browser the page is HTML5
It ensures the browser renders the page in standard mode
Why DOCTYPE is Important
1️⃣ Tells the browser the HTML version
2️⃣ Helps the browser render the page correctly
3️⃣ Prevents the browser from going into quirks mode (incorrect rendering)
✅ Simple Interview Answer
DOCTYPE is a declaration placed at the top of an HTML document that tells the browser which version of HTML is being used so the page can be displayed correctly.
Que 7) What if you remove <!DOCTYPE html> from your HTML?
----------------------------------------------------------------
If you remove <!DOCTYPE html>, the webpage will still open in the browser, but it may not display correctly.
This happens because the browser does not know which HTML version is being used.
What Happens When DOCTYPE is Removed
1️⃣ Browser enters Quirks Mode
The browser uses old rules to display the page.
2️⃣ Layout problems may occur
CSS and design may look different or break.
3️⃣ Compatibility issues
Different browsers may show the page differently.
4️⃣ Harder debugging
Developers may face problems while fixing errors.
Example Without DOCTYPE
<html>
<head>
<title>Example</title>
</head>
<body>
<h1>Hello</h1>
</body>
</html>
The page may still load, but rendering may not follow modern HTML standards.
✅ Simple Interview Answer
If <!DOCTYPE html> is removed, the browser may switch to quirks mode, which can cause layout, compatibility, and rendering issues because the browser cannot identify the HTML version.
Que 8) Difference between Head & Body in HTML? Where to place JS link reference?
Difference between <head> and <body>
--------------------------------------------
<head> Tag
The <head> section contains information about the webpage.
This information is not directly visible on the webpage.
It is used for metadata and settings.
Common things inside <head>:
<title> – page title shown in browser tab
<meta> – page information
<link> – CSS files
<script> – JavaScript files
Example:
<head>
<title>My Website</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body> Tag
The <body> section contains the actual content of the webpage.
Everything inside it is visible to the user.
Examples of content:
Headings
Paragraphs
Images
Buttons
Links
Example:
<body>
<h1>Welcome</h1>
<p>This is my website</p>
</body>
Difference Table
Head	Body
Contains page information	Contains visible content
Not visible to users	Visible to users
Includes title, meta, CSS	Includes text, images, buttons
Where to Place JavaScript Link Reference?
JavaScript can be placed in two places:
1️⃣ Inside <head>
<head>
<script src="script.js"></script>
</head>
But this may slow page loading because the browser loads JS before the page content.
2️⃣ Best Practice – Before </body>
<body>
<h1>Hello</h1>
<script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
✔ This is recommended because the page loads first, then JavaScript runs.
✅ Simple Interview Answer
The <head> tag contains metadata and page information that is not visible to users, while the <body> tag contains the visible
content of the webpage. JavaScript files are usually placed before the closing </body> tag for better page loading performance. 🚀
